Scanning `self.inputs` for a condition that should apply to the script's UTxO is insecure because any other input in the same transaction could satisfy the check. For example, if you look for 100 ADA in any input, an attacker can include a personal UTxO with 100 ADA and drain the script with an underfunded UTxO.

The correct pattern is to resolve the script's own input by its `OutputReference`:

```
use cardano/transaction
use cardano/assets

validator secure_check {
  spend(_datum, _redeemer, own_ref, self) {
    let own_input = transaction.resolve_input(self.inputs, own_ref)
    assets.lovelace_of(own_input.output.value) >= 10_000_000
  }
}
```

This binds the check exclusively to the UTxO being spent by this validator.

